
NSG (NETWORK SECURITY GROUP) 
========================

1.CREATE RESOURCE GROUP
2.LAUNCH/CREATE LINUX VM
3.Connect  vm
-> shift normal user to super user === sudo -i
4. refresh/update the terminal
-> apt-get update
5.install sample webpage
 -> apt-get install apache2 -y
6.copy public ip of vm paste into chrome
7.Enable http port no in nsg
8.custamize sample website
root directory = /var/www/html
<h1> Hi this is html webpage</h1>
<h2> server-01</h2>
<h3> server-02 </h3>

